03:17.865 --> 03:19.333
This...

03:19.367 --> 03:20.801
We could do it
in the warehouse.

03:20.834 --> 03:22.636
Dwight, excellent idea.
Go to the warehouse.

03:22.670 --> 03:24.405
Okay, fine.
Be actually perfect.

03:24.438 --> 03:25.706
Perfect!
You know what?

03:25.739 --> 03:28.809
There is another side
to this place, gentlemen.

03:28.842 --> 03:30.878
And I know we all love

03:30.911 --> 03:33.514
our cushy jobs and our fun,
exciting office.

03:33.547 --> 03:35.516
But do you realize
that underneath us

03:35.549 --> 03:36.817
there is another world.

03:36.850 --> 03:38.686
The warehouse world.

03:38.719 --> 03:41.989
A world that is teeming
with sweat and dirt

03:42.022 --> 03:43.691
and life.

03:43.724 --> 03:45.659
Life.

03:45.693 --> 03:47.328
The bowels of the office.

03:47.361 --> 03:48.696
These guys are down there.

03:48.729 --> 03:51.465
They are real men
doing real man's work.

03:51.499 --> 03:55.303
We are going to learn
how a warehouse works.

03:57.371 --> 03:59.039
Oh, I think this is gonna
work out great.

03:59.072 --> 04:01.809
